- rule_id: spans-candidates-filtered/sent_0009-f01f7475
  source:
    doc: spans_candidates_filtered
    citation: appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0009
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0009
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: risks not reasonably mitigable through design or technical information
  conditions:
  - when identifying risks for the high-risk AI system
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - developer must limit the risks addressed under this Article to only those risks
    that may be reasonably mitigated or eliminated through development or design of
    the high-risk AI system or through the provision of adequate technical information.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: '''Reasonably mitigated'' is subjective; no measurable criterion or artifact
      enables an objective pass/fail check.'
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
- rule_id: spans-candidates-filtered/sent_0009-62d16823
  source:
    doc: spans_candidates_filtered
    citation: appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0009
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0009
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: unconsidered interaction effects between requirements
  conditions:
  - when designing risk management measures
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - developer must give due consideration to the effects and possible interaction
    resulting from the combined application of the requirements set out in this Section
    when designing risk management measures, with a view to minimising risks while
    achieving an appropriate balance in implementing those measures.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Vague obligation ('give due consideration'/'appropriate balance') with
      no objective, inspectable artifact or predicate to verify compliance.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
    - ci_gate
- rule_id: spans-candidates-filtered/sent_0009-8c0275e0
  source:
    doc: spans_candidates_filtered
    citation: appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0009
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0009
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: unacceptable residual risk of high-risk AI system
  conditions:
  - when assessing residual risk associated with each hazard and overall system risk
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - developer must ensure that risk management measures are such that the relevant
    residual risk associated with each hazard and the overall residual risk of the
    high-risk AI system is judged to be acceptable.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Requires subjective judgment of 'acceptable' residual risk without measurable
      criteria or artifacts, so no objective oracle can verify pass/fail.
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-candidates-filtered/sent_0010-26faab3d
  source:
    doc: spans_candidates_filtered
    citation: appropriate-the-necessary-testing-and-reporting-processes-in/sent_0010
