    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain:
    - PII
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: retention of special-category personal data beyond necessity
  conditions:
  - processing special categories of personal data for bias detection and correction
    for high-risk AI systems
  - processing is strictly necessary
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider must delete the special categories of personal data once the bias has
    been corrected or once the personal data has reached the end of its retention
    period, whichever comes first
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: '''bias has been corrected'' lacks an objective, auditable signal to determine
      the required deletion timing.'
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - data_check
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-candidates-filtered/sent_0003-a513b90f
  source:
    doc: spans_candidates_filtered
    citation: directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/directive-eu-2016/680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain:
    - PII
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: unauthorized access or misuse of special categories of personal data
  conditions:
  - when processing special categories of personal data for bias detection and correction
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider must apply measures to ensure the personal data processed are secured,
    protected and subject to suitable safeguards, including strict controls and documentation
    of access, to avoid misuse and ensure that only authorised persons have access
    with appropriate confidentiality obligations.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Mandates access controls, access documentation and authorized-only access—verifiable
      via configs, audit logs, access records and data/classification metadata.
    evidence_signals:
    - config_check
    - log_check
    - repo_check
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-candidates-filtered/sent_0003-2bdf5ba5
  source:
    doc: spans_candidates_filtered
    citation: directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0003
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/directive-eu-2016/680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0003
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain:
    - PII
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: lack of documented justification for processing special categories of personal
    data
  conditions:
  - when processing special categories of personal data for bias detection and correction
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider must ensure records of processing activities include the reasons why
    the processing of special categories of personal data was strictly necessary to
    detect and correct biases, and why that objective could not be achieved by processing
    other data.
  evidence:
  - records of processing activities (reasons for necessity)
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Verify by inspecting records of processing activities (documents) for
      required justifications stored in code/docs repository.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-candidates-filtered/sent_0006-4462d8aa
  source:
    doc: spans_candidates_filtered
    citation: directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0006
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0006
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: placement on the market without technical documentation
  conditions:
  - before the system is placed on the market or put into service
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - developer must draw up the technical documentation before the system is placed
    on the market or put into service.
  evidence:
  - technical documentation
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Explicit obligation with actor and timing; documentation existence and
      timestamps relative to deployment are verifiable.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
    - ci_gate
    - log_check
- rule_id: spans-candidates-filtered/sent_0006-16ee3658
  source:
    doc: spans_candidates_filtered
    citation: directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0006
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0006
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: outdated technical documentation
  conditions:
  - after the system is placed on the market or put into service
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - developer must keep the technical documentation up-to-date.
  evidence:
  - technical documentation
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Vague 'up-to-date' obligation lacks measurable criteria (timing/metrics);
      cannot be objectively checked.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
    - ci_gate
    - io_check
- rule_id: spans-candidates-filtered/sent_0006-397f68a0
  source:
    doc: spans_candidates_filtered
    citation: directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0006
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0006
  scope:
    actor:
    - developer
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: authorities unable to assess compliance due to insufficient documentation
  conditions:
  - when assessed by national competent authorities or notified bodies
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - developer must prepare the technical documentation to demonstrate that the high-risk
    AI system complies with the requirements set out in this Section and to provide
    national competent authorities and notified bodies with the necessary information
    in a clear and comprehensive form to assess compliance.
  evidence:
  - technical documentation
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: 'Obligation is vague: ''demonstrate compliance'' and ''clear and comprehensive''
      lack objective criteria for a pass/fail check.'
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
    - io_check
- rule_id: spans-candidates-filtered/sent_0008-9b641b6f
  source:
    doc: spans_candidates_filtered
    citation: directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0008
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0008
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: non-demonstrable regulatory non-compliance
  conditions:
  - for high-risk AI systems
  - to enable assessment by national competent authorities and notified bodies
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider must draw up technical documentation in such a way that it demonstrates
    the high-risk AI system complies with the requirements set out in this Section
    and provides national competent authorities and notified bodies with the necessary
    information in a clear and comprehensive form to assess compliance
  evidence:
  - technical documentation (Annex IV elements)
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Requires documentation but lacks concrete objective criteria (e.g., required
      contents), so pass/fail cannot be measured.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-candidates-filtered/sent_0008-b41c9ef5
  source:
    doc: spans_candidates_filtered
    citation: directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0008
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0008
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: incomplete technical documentation
  conditions:
  - for high-risk AI systems
  exceptions:
  - SMEs, including start-ups, may provide the elements of the technical documentation
    specified in Annex IV in a simplified manner
  requirements:
  - provider must ensure the technical documentation contains at a minimum the elements
    set out in Annex IV
  evidence:
  - technical documentation (Annex IV elements)
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Obligation to include Annex IV elements can be verified by inspecting
      provider technical documentation artifacts (repo_check).
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-candidates-filtered/sent_0010-0a09e15f
  source:
    doc: spans_candidates_filtered
