- rule_id: spans-candidates-filtered/sent_0012-c180d896
  source:
    doc: spans_candidates_filtered
    citation: directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0012
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/directive-eu-2016-680-all-the-following-conditions-must-be-m/sent_0012
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
    - prod
  hazard: insufficient technical documentation for high-risk AI systems
  conditions:
  - where a high-risk AI system related to a product covered by the Union harmonisation
    legislation listed in Section A of Annex I is placed on the market or put into
    service
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider must draw up a single set of technical documentation containing all the
    information set out in paragraph 1 and the information required under those legal
    acts when the specified high-risk AI system is placed on the market or put into
    service.
  evidence:
  - technical documentation
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Provider must produce a single technical documentation at market entry;
      existence and contents can be checked in repo/artifact records.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
    - data_check
