- rule_id: spans-candidates-filtered/sent_0008-1c82685e
  source:
    doc: spans_candidates_filtered
    citation: article-12/sent_0008
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/article-12/sent_0008
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: deployers inability to use system safely
  conditions:
  - for high-risk AI systems
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider must provide instructions for use in an appropriate digital format or
    otherwise that are concise, complete, correct and clear and that are relevant,
    accessible and comprehensible to deployers.
  evidence:
  - instructions for use
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Obligation uses subjective qualities (concise, complete, correct, comprehensible);
      no objective pass/fail criteria or measurable artifacts specified.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
- rule_id: spans-candidates-filtered/sent_0008-c2f31eef
  source:
    doc: spans_candidates_filtered
    citation: article-12/sent_0008
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/article-12/sent_0008
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: inability to contact provider
  conditions:
  - for high-risk AI systems
  - in the instructions for use
  exceptions:
  - where applicable
  requirements:
  - provider must include its identity and contact details and, where applicable,
    the identity and contact details of its authorised representative in the instructions
    for use.
  evidence:
  - instructions for use
  severity: medium
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Check instructions for use to confirm required provider and authorised
      representative identity/contact details are present.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
- rule_id: spans-candidates-filtered/sent_0008-e48651eb
  source:
    doc: spans_candidates_filtered
    citation: article-12/sent_0008
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/article-12/sent_0008
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: use outside intended purpose
  conditions:
  - for high-risk AI systems
  - in the instructions for use
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider must include the characteristics, capabilities and limitations of performance
    of the high-risk AI system, including its intended purpose, in the instructions
    for use.
  evidence:
  - instructions for use
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Requires providers to include specified characteristics and intended purpose
      in instructions; verifiable by inspecting the product's instructions/documentation
      (repo_check).
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-candidates-filtered/sent_0008-13935c3e
  source:
    doc: spans_candidates_filtered
    citation: article-12/sent_0008
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/article-12/sent_0008
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: deployers unaware of expected accuracy, robustness or cybersecurity levels
  conditions:
  - for high-risk AI systems
  - in the instructions for use
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider must include the level of accuracy, including its metrics, and the robustness
    and cybersecurity against which the high-risk AI system has been tested and validated
    and which can be expected, in the instructions for use.
  evidence:
  - instructions for use
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Verify by inspecting the product's instructions-for-use documentation
      for stated accuracy metrics, robustness, and cybersecurity testing/expected
      levels.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-candidates-filtered/sent_0001-c4fd31bc
  source:
    doc: spans_candidates_filtered
    citation: v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0001
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: insufficient human oversight causing misuse
  conditions:
  - referred to in Article 14
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider must include the human oversight measures referred to in Article 14,
    including the technical measures put in place to facilitate the interpretation
    of the outputs of the high-risk AI system by deployers.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Refers to Article 14 and vague 'facilitate interpretation' without measurable
      criteria; no objective oracle to determine pass/fail.
    evidence_signals:
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-candidates-filtered/sent_0001-884e0779
  source:
    doc: spans_candidates_filtered
    citation: v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0001
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: misinterpretation of outputs by deployers
  conditions:
  - where applicable
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider must provide information that enables deployers to interpret the outputs
    of the high-risk AI system and use them appropriately.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Vague adequacy requirement; no objective artifact or measurable criterion
      to verify whether provided information enables correct interpretation.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-candidates-filtered/sent_0001-61280de4
  source:
    doc: spans_candidates_filtered
    citation: v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0001
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: improper functioning due to insufficient resources, maintenance, or logging
  conditions:
  - where relevant
  - in accordance with Article 12
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider must specify the computational and hardware resources needed and the
    expected lifetime of the high-risk AI system, must specify any necessary maintenance
    and care measures including their frequency and software update requirements,
    and where relevant must describe mechanisms that allow deployers to properly collect,
    store and interpret the logs in accordance with Article 12.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Obligates providers to publish specs (resources, lifetime, maintenance,
      logging) which can be inspected in configs/docs.
    evidence_signals:
    - config_check
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-candidates-filtered/sent_0001-ec3e1e12
  source:
    doc: spans_candidates_filtered
    citation: v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0001
    span_id: EU_AI_2024_removed/v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context:
    - high-risk
  hazard: unequal or unsafe performance across specific persons or groups
  conditions:
  - when appropriate
  - on which the system is intended to be used
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider must include, when appropriate, the system's performance regarding specific
    persons or groups of persons on which the system is intended to be used.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: '''When appropriate'' is vague; no objective criterion to determine when
      or what group-specific performance must be included.'
    evidence_signals:
    - config_check
    - io_check
- rule_id: spans-candidates-filtered/sent_0001-a0a2f8eb
  source:
    doc: spans_candidates_filtered
    citation: v-when-appropriate-its-performance-regarding-specific-person/sent_0001
